cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC

The paper deals with Behavioral Signal Processing (BSP) tasks using Deep Neural Networks (DNN) and focuses on behavior recognition from speech in the mental health domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also deals with machine learning tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for dealing with limited data, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on mental health suggests that it could belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
